@Empact Looking at that PR, it seems like that logic was only added to `travis_retry` and not `travis_wait`.  When this first happened I [posted on their forums](https://travis-ci.community/t/no-output-logged-when-using-travis-wait-command/1909/2) to get some clarification and their staff pointed out the `errexit` conflict.

Also, looking at the `travis_wait` command on Travis master, seems to not catch errors
https://github.com/travis-ci/travis-build/blob/4f580b238530108cdd08719c326cd571d4e7b99f/lib/travis/build/bash/travis_wait.bash#L13
